The paper deals with lower bounds for distributed algorithms in the radio network model, which is a topic that falls under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC). The paper also involves communication problems and network topology, which are relevant to the sub-category of Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). Information Theory (cs.IT) is another relevant sub-category, as the paper deals with the efficiency of communication strategies. Game Theory (cs.GT) is also relevant, as the paper introduces a new technique based on a probabilistic hitting game. Finally, the paper involves analyzing the performance of algorithms, which falls under the sub-category of Social and Information Networks (cs.SI).
